sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Markus Neis, FPT.EagleEye Team, Vadim Khrykov, Cyb3rEng, Michael Haag, Christopher Peacock @securepeacock, @scythe_io

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Windows Shell/Scripting Processes Spawning Suspicious Programs
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects suspicious child processes of a Windows shell and scripting processes such as wscript, rundll32, powershell, mshta...etc.
Detects scheduled task creations or modification on a suspicious schedule type

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Script Interpreter Execution From Suspicious Folder

sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Script Execution From Temp Folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a suspicious script executions from temporary folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Max Altgelt (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Command Patterns In Scheduled Task Creation
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects scheduled task creation using "schtasks" that contain potentially suspicious or uncommon commands

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Scheduled Task Creation Involving Temp Folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of scheduled tasks that involves a temporary folder and runs only once

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Schedule Task Creation From Env Variable Or Potentially Suspicious Path Via Schtasks.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects Schtask creations that point to a suspicious folder or an environment variable often used by malware
